# AYRA Python runtime

Python is a **required** part of the AYRA stack â€” not optional. The Node worker and dashboard call a local Python sidecar for cron blueprints, schedule validation, and Hermes-compatible automation logic.

## Setup

From repo root (also runs during `npm run setup`):

```bash
npm run python:setup
```

Or manually:

```bash
pip install -e python/
```

Requires **Python 3.9+** on PATH (or set `AYRA_PYTHON_BIN` in `.env`).

## Runtime

The worker auto-starts the sidecar on port **8765** (override with `AYRA_PYTHON_PORT` / `AYRA_PYTHON_URL`).

Foreground (debug):

```bash
npm run python:runtime
```

Health check:

```bash
curl http://127.0.0.1:8765/health
```

## Skill bundles

SKILL.md playbooks live in repo-root `skills/` and are synced to `python/ayra/skills/bundles/`:

```bash
npm run sync:python   # after editing agent/, cron/, or skills/ at repo root
```

See [docs/ayra-python-sync-manifest.md](../docs/ayra-python-sync-manifest.md) for the sync list.

Executable TS skills: `src/lib/skills/` (e.g. `polymarket-search`, `arxiv-search`).

## Telegram gateway (Python)

When `AYRA_TELEGRAM_PYTHON=true` (default), the worker auto-starts `python -m ayra.telegram_gateway`:

- **Ingress/egress:** `python-telegram-bot` (Hermes-style)
- **Agent logic:** Node worker via `http://127.0.0.1:8790/internal/telegram/dispatch`

Debug foreground:

```bash
npm run worker          # starts internal API + Python gateway
npm run python:telegram # gateway only (worker must be running)
```

Legacy TypeScript polling: `AYRA_TELEGRAM_PYTHON=false` + `TELEGRAM_POLLING=true`.

## HTTP API (cron runtime)

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/health` | Liveness |
| GET | `/v1/blueprints` | Full blueprint + suggestion catalog |
| POST | `/v1/blueprints/fill` | Validate slots â†’ job spec |
| POST | `/v1/cron/next` | Next run time (croniter) |

TypeScript client: `src/lib/python/runtime-client.ts`

## Layout

```
python/ayra/
  runtime_server.py   # HTTP sidecar (entry: python -m ayra.runtime_server)
  ayra_constants.py
  ayra_time.py
  cron/               # Blueprint catalog, jobs, suggestions
  agent/              # retry_utils, iteration_budget, skill_bundles
```

## Sync from repo root

Edit `agent/`, `cron/`, or `skills/` at the repository root, then:

```bash
npm run sync:python
npm run python:setup
```

## Environment

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `AYRA_HOME` | `~/.ayra` | Python data directory |
| `AYRA_PYTHON_URL` | `http://127.0.0.1:8765` | Sidecar base URL |
| `AYRA_PYTHON_REQUIRED` | `true` | Fail worker/API if runtime unavailable |

## TypeScript integration

- Worker: `ensurePythonRuntime()` in `src/workers/agent-worker.ts`
- Cron API: proxies catalog/fill to Python
- Brain worker: reschedules via Python `cron/next`

Dashboard UI still uses Next.js; Python owns blueprint **logic** (single source of truth).
